    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_004/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "we benchmark the state-of-the-art models on the new METLIN-CCS database and assess their generalizability. We also demonstrate increased generalizability using an extension of SigmaCCS, which we call Mol2CCS, that incorporates additional information such as instrument type.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper compares GNN architectures (GraphCCS, SigmaCCS, Mol2CCS) but does NOT evaluate GAT or MPNN. Instead, paper extends SigmaCCS with additional features (Mol2CCS) and compares to GraphCCS and original SigmaCCS. The comparison is on the same dataset split, but alternative architectures named in card (GAT, MPNN) are not evaluated.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-024-00899-w",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_004",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How do alternative graph neural network architectures (e.g., GAT, MPNN) compare to the original GNN architecture in predicting collision cross section on the same dataset split?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:16:33.308952+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_004/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We employed correlation metrics such as coefficient of determination (R2), Pearson and Spearman correlation. Additionally, we used mean absolute error (MAE), mean squared error (MSE), root mean squared error (RMSE), relative standard deviation (RSD), and the relative error in percentage between the predicted CCS values and the experimental ones (% CCS error).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper reports RMSE, MAE, R\u00b2, and other metrics in comparative tables/figures (Figs. 2, 3, 4) for multiple GNN models. However, paper does NOT report training time or inference speed metrics. Metrics are presented in figures/supplementary tables, not explicitly as CSV/JSON files.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-024-00899-w",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_004",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Comparative performance table (CSV or JSON) with metrics (RMSE, MAE, accuracy, training time, inference speed) for both original and alternative GNN architectures",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:16:33.308952+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
