    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/graph-neural-network-architecture-implementation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We trained and tested each model on train and test splits using the following strategy. First, we divided the entire dataset (CCSBase and METLIN-CCS data combined) into five distinct groups: lipids, dimers carbohydrates, peptides, and everything else. This categorization ensured that each of these categories was represented in the train and test sets. We performed an 80/20 train test split on each of these groups stratified on the Murcko scaffold.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses fixed 80/20 train/test splits stratified by Murcko scaffold for CCS prediction task.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-024-00899-w",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "graph-neural-network-architecture-implementation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "You have a baseline GNN model trained on a molecular property prediction task (e.g., collision cross section) with fixed train/validation/test splits",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:19:40.778129+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/graph-neural-network-architecture-implementation/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The first model, SigmaCCS [6], employs Edge-Conditioned Convolutions (ECCs) [19] to embed the original molecular structure along with the adduct type. The second GNN, GraphCCS [22], simulates the structure of the resulting adduct and uses it as input for a Graph Convolutional Network (GCN).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper compares Edge-Conditioned Convolutions (ECC) and Graph Convolutional Networks (GCN), which are message-passing variants, but does NOT include attention-based architectures (GAT) or explicit MPNN implementations as claimed in the card.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-024-00899-w",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "graph-neural-network-architecture-implementation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "alternative message-passing or attention-based graph architectures",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:19:40.778129+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
