    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/graph-neural-network-architecture-implementation/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We evaluated the performance of the models on a test set using several metrics. We employed correlation metrics such as coefficient of determination (R2), Pearson and Spearman correlation. Additionally, we used mean absolute error (MAE), mean squared error (MSE), root mean squared error (RMSE), relative standard deviation (RSD), and the relative error in percentage between the predicted CCS values and the experimental ones (% CCS error).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses comprehensive standardized regression metrics (R\u00b2, MAE, RMSE, MRE, Pearson/Spearman correlation) for model evaluation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-024-00899-w",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "graph-neural-network-architecture-implementation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "standardized regression metrics",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:19:40.778129+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/graph-neural-network-architecture-implementation/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We benchmarked all the models using three different settings. In the first setting, we trained each model on 80% of one database (METLIN-CCS or CCSBase) and tested it on the remaining 20% of the same database.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly evaluates models on held-out test sets using multiple evaluation strategies.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-024-00899-w",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "graph-neural-network-architecture-implementation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "methods",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "held-out test performance comparison",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:19:40.778129+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/graph-neural-network-model-inference/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "we benchmark the state-of-the-art models on the new METLIN-CCS database and assess their generalizability. We also demonstrate increased generalizability using an extension of SigmaCCS, which we call Mol2CCS, that incorporates additional information such as instrument type. Finally, we show that using confidence models to filter predictions can result in increased performance of the models.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper demonstrates GNN model inference and prediction on molecular graphs (SigmaCCS, GraphCCS, Mol2CCS), but does NOT perform post-hoc attribution studies, ablation studies, or gradient-based saliency mapping to identify which molecular features drive CCS predictions. The paper uses confidence models to filter predictions but does not conduct feature importance analysis via the methods claimed in the card.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-024-00899-w",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "graph-neural-network-model-inference",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Load a trained graph neural network model and use it to generate predictions on molecular structures represented as graphs. This skill enables post-hoc analysis of GNN predictions, such as attribution studies to identify which molecular features drive collision cross section pred",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:19:59.333677+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/graph-neural-network-model-inference/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The SigmaCCS architecture consists of a GNN with three ECC layers [19] trained on three matrices representing the molecular graph described in Section 'Feature extraction for Mol2CCS'. The output of these layers is concatenated with a one-hot encoded vector representing the adduct and fed into several fully connected layers to produce a predicted ccs value.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly describes loading and executing GNN models (SigmaCCS, GraphCCS, Mol2CCS) on molecular graph representations to generate CCS predictions.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-024-00899-w",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "graph-neural-network-model-inference",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Load a trained graph neural network model and use it to generate predictions on molecular structures represented as graphs.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:19:59.333677+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
