      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To construct them, we first read the SMILES representation of each molecule using RDKit (v2023.09.5) [8] and subsequently used the ETKDG and MMFF94 conformer generators to obtain the 3D conformers for each molecule. Lastly, from these conformers, we obtained the atoms, bonds and their attributes.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper constructs molecular graphs from SMILES and extracts atom/bond features, but does NOT explicitly describe serialization to .pt or .pkl formats. The paper describes feature extraction and model training but does not mention serialization workflows or storage formats for graph tensors.",
