      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "we benchmark the state-of-the-art models on the new METLIN-CCS database and assess their generalizability. We also demonstrate increased generalizability using an extension of SigmaCCS, which we call Mol2CCS, that incorporates additional information such as instrument type.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper does compare multiple GNN architectures (GraphCCS, SigmaCCS, Mol2CCS) on the same task (CCS prediction) with maintained input/output structure. However, the paper does NOT implement Graph Attention Networks or generalized Message-Passing Neural Networks as alternatives. Instead, it extends SigmaCCS (which uses Edge-Conditioned Convolutions) with additional feature modules. The comparison is between existing published models, not a systematic exploration of alternative message-passing mechanisms as drop-in replacements.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-024-00899-w",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
