    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/message-passing-variant-selection-and-adaptation/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We evaluated the performance of the models on a test set using several metrics. We employed correlation metrics such as coefficient of determination (R2), Pearson and Spearman correlation. Additionally, we used mean absolute error (MAE), mean squared error (MSE), root mean squared error (RMSE), relative standard deviation (RSD), and the relative error in percentage between the predicted CCS values and the experimental ones (% CCS error).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper does provide comprehensive regression accuracy metrics (R\u00b2, MAE, RMSE, MRE) comparing three models (GraphCCS, SigmaCCS, Mol2CCS). However, inference speed and training efficiency are not reported or compared.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-024-00899-w",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "message-passing-variant-selection-and-adaptation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Direct performance comparison of alternative GNN architectures on regression accuracy, inference speed, or training efficiency",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:20:47.901174+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/message-passing-variant-selection-and-adaptation/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We trained and tested each model on train and test splits using the following strategy. First, we divided the entire dataset (CCSBase and METLIN-CCS data combined) into five distinct groups: lipids, dimers carbohydrates, peptides, and everything else. This categorization ensured that each of these categories was represented in the train and test sets. We performed an 80/20 train test split on each of these groups stratified on the Murcko scaffold.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly maintains consistent 80/20 stratified splits across all models evaluated.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-024-00899-w",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "message-passing-variant-selection-and-adaptation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "methods",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Maintain identical train/validation/test splits across all model variants",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:20:47.901174+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/message-passing-variant-selection-and-adaptation/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Since Mol2CCS is an extension of SigmaCCS [6], we expanded upon its codebase for its implementation. Our goal, rather than developing a new model, was to demonstrate how current SOTA models can be improved by leveraging additional features... The SigmaCCS architecture consists of a GNN with three ECC layers [19] trained on three matrices representing the molecular graph... In our implementation of Mol2CCS, the GNN module is identical to SigmaCCS's implementation, but we extend the model with a parallel module consisting of four fully connected layers",
      "asbval:note": "Mol2CCS maintains the same GNN core as SigmaCCS but adds parallel feature processing modules. The final output (predicted CCS value) is identical, but the internal architecture is extended rather than being a true drop-in replacement with maintained dimensionality throughout.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-024-00899-w",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "message-passing-variant-selection-and-adaptation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "methods",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Maintain input/output dimensionality across baseline and alternative models",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:20:47.901174+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/model-generalizability-assessment/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We benchmarked all the models using three different settings. In the first setting, we trained each model on 80% of one database (METLIN-CCS or CCSBase) and tested it on the remaining 20% of the same database... We evaluated the performance of the models on a test set using several metrics. We employed correlation metrics such as coefficient of determination (R2), Pearson and Spearman correlation. Additionally, we used mean absolute error (MAE), mean squared error (MSE), root mean squared error (RMSE), relative standard deviation (RSD), and the relative error in percentage between the predicted CCS values and the experimental ones (% CCS error).",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly evaluates GNN models (GraphCCS, SigmaCCS, Mol2CCS) on held-out test data using RMSE, MAE, and R\u00b2 metrics, directly matching the research question.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-024-00899-w",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "model-generalizability-assessment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Evaluate whether a trained graph neural network model for collision cross section prediction generalizes effectively to held-out test data by computing standard regression metrics (RMSE, MAE, R\u00b2) and comparing against baseline values.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:21:09.047237+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/model-generalizability-assessment/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In this setting, the performance significantly drops across all models; thus, indicating the lack of generality of the models when predicting within an unseen chemical space... These results can be used as a proxy to assess the performance of a model in a more realistic application, when the model has not seen closely similar molecules to the ones it is to predict.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly addresses generalization across diverse molecular datasets and demonstrates performance degradation on novel chemical spaces, validating the importance of this assessment.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s13321-024-00899-w",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "model-generalizability-assessment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This skill is essential for validating whether GNN models can reliably predict CCS across diverse molecular datasets beyond their training distribution.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T13:21:09.047237+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
